	<p>
		<strong>Transit Observer</strong> documents ongoing security research, infrastructure forensics,
		and deep dives into systems code.
	</p>

	<h3>Series</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Infrastructure MITM Investigation</strong> — An ISP subscriber investigates
			anomalous network behavior targeting LLM provider connections. Tcpdump analysis, TTL forensics,
			and the case for a transparent TCP proxy at the ISP-to-transit boundary.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Actually Reading jart/cosmopolitan</strong> — One file at a time through Justine Tunney's
			cosmopolitan libc. Each entry builds on the last. No skimming, no summaries — actually reading the code.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Author</h3>
	<p>
		Written by Vincent L. Anderson. Published via GitHub Pages.
	</p>
